      "title": "Production file-list drift detection is disabled for runner-created completions",
      "evidence": "The production hook treats an empty allowed_file_globs/scope.paths list as no drift. The runner writes every completion with \"scope\": {}, so any matching production_edit_review_completion allows all production .go files in the same cycle/base/tier instead of only reviewed files.",
      "recommendation": "Have the runner record the reviewed file set/globs in the completion, and make the production hook deny when scope is missing or empty. Empty scope should mean invalid completion, not unlimited scope.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-production-trigger.sh:120"
