      "title": "Stop hook cannot enforce unresolved review obligations because triggers never create pending obligations",
      "evidence": "session-stop-review.sh only blocks when it finds artifact entries with status == pending, but the three PreToolUse triggers only emit deny JSON and never append a pending obligation entry. A blocked plan/test/production review therefore leaves no pending record for the Stop hook to find.",
      "recommendation": "Either have trigger hooks atomically record pending obligations before denying, or have the Stop hook recompute outstanding obligations from current cycle state and recent denials instead of relying on pending artifact entries.",
